# Cline workspace rules — buddee-health-hippocrates

## graphify (code knowledge graph)

This project has a knowledge graph at `graphify-out/` with god nodes,
community structure, and cross-file relationships. Use it as the FIRST stop
for codebase questions — it returns a scoped subgraph that is usually much
smaller and more precise than raw grep output.

Rules:
- For codebase questions, first query the graph. Prefer the graphify MCP
  tools when the graphify MCP server is connected (`query_graph`,
  `get_neighbors`, `shortest_path`, `get_community`); otherwise run the CLI:
  `~/.local/bin/graphify query "<question>"`.
- Use `~/.local/bin/graphify path "<A>" "<B>"` (or MCP `shortest_path`) for
  relationships between two symbols/files and
  `~/.local/bin/graphify explain "<concept>"` for focused concepts.
- If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, use it for broad navigation instead
  of raw source browsing.
- Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` only for broad architecture review or
  when query/path/explain do not surface enough context.
- After modifying code, run `~/.local/bin/graphify update .` to keep the
  graph current (AST-only extraction, no LLM/API cost).
- If `graphify-out/graph.json` is missing or the CLI is unavailable, fall
  back to search_codebase / grep and mention that the graph needs a rebuild.

## Security posture (do not regress)

- This is a HIPAA-adjacent clinical coding platform. Never weaken the BAA /
  PHI gates in `core/phi_guard.py`, the prompt-boundary escaping in
  `core/agent.py`, or the tenant RLS + `GucStamper` pattern in
  `core/db_session.py` without explicit instruction and a matching test.
- Every auth-relevant change (login, invites, API keys, scopes, JWT) must
  ship with tests, including at least one adversarial case in
  `tests/test_adversarial_probe.py` style.
- Secrets never go into the repo. `BUDDI_BAA_CONFIRMED` stays `0` everywhere
  except the counsel-cleared production PHI tier.

## Validation before declaring done

- Backend: `./venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -q` must pass; new modules
  must pass `./venv/bin/python -m ruff check <files>`.
- Frontend: `cd frontend && npx eslint <changed files>` and
  `npm run build` must pass.
